    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade 1995 Mazda RX-7 FD, a pinnacle of 90s JDM engineering. This specimen retains its original 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, delivering linear power through the factory five-speed manual gearbox. Mechanical integrity is paramount: compression test results remain at factory spec, and the complex vacuum line 'rat's nest' has been meticulously maintained to ensure seamless turbo transition. The chassis features the original double-wishbone suspension geometry with zero bushing play, preserving its legendary 50/50 weight distribution. Finished in pristine Montego Blue over a flawless Tan leather interior, this vehicle shows no signs of heat-cycling fatigue in the plastics or oxidation on the undercarriage. A turn-key investment for the discerning enthusiast seeking visceral analog performance.",
